@node whatis "What is PowerWEB?"

    @{u}What is this@{uu}?


    @{b}PowerWEB@{ub}  is a little tool which will simplify the life of all who
    want to run a WEB server.

    Well, it all started when I installed The Apache Web server on  my
    amiga (A GREAT server btw) BUT for the avarage beginner, apache is
    a  bit difficult,  and  believe  me, ITS  NOT VERY FAST EITHER.

    So after  having  used  the webserver for about a year, I decidede
    to write my own server :)

@endnode

@node req "System Requirements"

    @{u}Requirements@{uu}:


    To use @{b}PowerWEB@{ub} you need the following stuff:


    Ę  Amiga OS 3.0 or greater

    Ę  a Hard Disk
       (@{b}PowerWEB@{ub} is useless without a hard disk)

    Ę  An Amiga with a 68000+ CPU

    Ę  AmiTCP 3+ or Miami 2.96+

@endnode

@node install "Installation"

    @{u}Installation@{uu}:


    @{b}PowerWEB@{ub}  was  made  to be running under AmiTCP and miami.
    
    @{b}PowerWEB@{ub} comes  with an installer script. It will install all the
    things to get the server up and running.

    If  you,  for  some  reason,  wants to do the manual installation,
    here's how to do that:

    @{u}AmiTCP users only@{uu}:

    Ę  Copy  the @{b}PowerWEB@{ub} executable file to your Amitcp:serv

    Ę  Assign @{b}PowerWEB@{ub} to a location on your harddrive.

    Ę  Create a new drawer in PowerWEB: called HTML

    Ę  Copy  your  homepage  to  PowerWEB:HTML/ or use the sample html
       file.

    Ę  Check  if  the line 'http 80/tcp' is present in your amitcp:db/
       services file. If not - add it.

    Ę  Check if the line 'http    stream  tcp nowait      root    
       amitcp:serv/PowerWEB' is present  in  your amitcp:db/inetd.conf
       file. If not - add it.
    

    @{u}Miami users only@{uu}:

    Ę  Copy  the @{b}PowerWEB@{ub} executable file to the Miami directory.

    Ę  Assign @{b}PowerWEB@{ub} to a location on your harddrive.

    Ę  Create a new drawer in PowerWEB: called HTML

    Ę  Copy  your  homepage  to  PowerWEB:HTML/ or use the sample html
       file.

    Ę  Start Miami and enter the database section.

    Ę  Check  if the line 'http 80/tcp' is present in services. If not
       - add it.

    Ę  Check if the line 'http    stream  tcp nowait      root    
       Miami:PowerWEB/PowerWEB' is present  in inetd. If not - add it.

    Ę  Save the settings.


    Now the server should be ready to serve.

@endnode

